"Commercial License Agreement" means a written agreement, order form, or
other written authorization issued or accepted by the Licensor that grants
Commercial Use of a specified version or distribution of the Software.

"Commercial Use" means use of the Software in a production, operational,
revenue-generating, customer-facing, or externally delivered workflow. It
also includes embedding the Software in a product or service made available
to a third party.

"Production Use" means execution of the Software in a live or operational
environment used to perform work, deliver results, or support a business
process, whether or not that environment is directly exposed to a customer.

"Evaluation Use" means internal evaluation, research, testing, security
review, and development work that does not provide the Software's functionality
to external users and does not place the Software in a production workflow.

"Licensee Application" means an application or service developed by Licensee
that uses the Software as an internal component and whose primary purpose is
not to offer the Software itself as a standalone product or service.

"Competitive Service" means a product or service whose primary purpose is to
provide semiconductor design flow orchestration, project runtime, artifact
ledger, or equivalent EDA workflow functionality substantially similar to the
Software.

"Third-Party Components" means code, data, tools, or other materials that are
identified as third-party or are obtained from a dependency listed in the
package manifest. Third-Party Components are governed by their own licenses.

